\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well it's Robert Wilson only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Is 51 Ribbledale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And your marital status? You're divorced aren't you - or - separated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, I don't want anything to do with that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Divorced or separated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Divorced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It was '28.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 1899. May the twenty-first. Whit - Whit Sunday, I'm a twin. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Another boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 A broth - another boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Whereabouts were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Borbanks Rose Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 In Liverpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Just - Mossley Hill dairy it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You haven't moved far have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, I lived there 'til I was twelve. In Borbank. And we sold - my father bought another dairy at Hillside Dairy - you know where Digb
y the chemist is? Well that was our dairy and we went up in there in - the November of 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How many years there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It took you beyond your childhood obviously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lor' yes. Oh - after the - a long while - a long, long while after the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Why did the family make this first move when you were twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - you see my father and - and uncles - brothers were together. My uncle lived in a private house here at fifty Rose Lane and he used to come to the dairy We
ll he has a son and a daughter and there was - living was three sisters and myself. Father and mother and we were getting older and we branched out into two places and uncle went and lived at Borbank where I was born and we went to Hillside Dairy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So we'll talk about the first house - that's the house you remember mainly as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You'd really have been in the first house longer as a child wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Altogether? Ten. Eight - eight girls and two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What were the range of ages - can you start from the youngest of the family and work your way up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lor'. No - well the youngest girl, Eva, that's the one on there - see the - they - I think t
hey all lived but two after I was born. Before me we had four girls, father had - and father buried two little girls, one died at night and one in the morning and left them without a child and that was when - dysentery was very bad in here. The two little
 girls - one was nineteen months and the other was three months. And they were both put in the same coffin and died - buried and they were buried in Smithdown Road Cemetery. And then we came on the scene.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You were the first after these two little girls died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They were before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Oh there was four little girls before us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What difference in ages would there have been between those girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh I - I should think there would be perhaps fourteen - thirteen or fourteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Between each of the four girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And then when you came along how much younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I - now that I couldn't say - I should think there'd be probably eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And what about the ones that came after you - what spacing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - there's - I believe there was one - for - I think there was one - two stillborn I think. I'm not sure. Then come Hilda which is fifteen months after me. Then Margaret - then there's one between Margaret and I - Marga
ret is about - six years younger than me and Eva would be - about eighteen months - two years after that. Oh of course those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They - had big family's didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How old was your father when you were born - can you work that out for me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lord. Now then - I haven't got a clue, I'm awfully sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Roughly - middle thirties - early thirties?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh he'd be - he'd be in his thirties, must have been. Well - wait half a minute. Well I was born in 1890 - I wa
s born in 1899. I'm seventy-one this year. Right, well me father died in '38 and he was sixty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So we decided your father was about thirty - in his early thirties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, he must have been about thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
He came from Howgill. Well it's in - on the border of Westmorland and Yorkshire. A farm. Yes. And he was thirteen when he came to Liverpool. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Farming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 He was farming when he first came here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, he was
 a farmer all his life, yes. We - actually my grandfather's first place when father - father came to stay with his cousin first in Woottan -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11493132\charrsid5983795  Foster. You know Foster's dairy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 s? Well that's where - at Newstead Farm and me grandfather then bought - bought a pl
ace where the bridge stands now in Bridge Road over the railway. That was the end of Bridge Road. Well then - we were there - I believe they were there - for a few years and the railway company wanted to build the - extra lines and they bought us - bought
 him out and he built Bowerbank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I didn't realize he was farming here - it's incredible isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Oh yes. Well - there was - you'll notice in the dairy there there's a window in the side of the house into the kitchen which was made for my grandmo
ther so she could watch them bowling on the opposite side of the road. The bowling green was there. That's where those redbrick houses are you know. That - well she was an invalid I believe. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Was he always a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Up to the time he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lor', yes. Well he retired - he retired of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did he also do any casual or part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, no. We'd plenty to do with our own cows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember your father ever being out of work - he was a self employed farmer so this would not have arisen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How old was your mother when you were born - was she roughly the same age as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I think she was two or three years younger but I wouldn't be certain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 In her very late twenties then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, oh she'd be her late twenties, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 From Portobello. In - out - in - in Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Had she any jobs before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12061119 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 She started work in Liverpool as 
an apprentice to - at the Adelphi as a cook and she finished up as a pastry cook there. And then she worked for Bertie Kane the brewer and that's where father, serving them with milk, met my mother. And they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12061119 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795  there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What about part time jobs - did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12061119 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795  or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Good Lord, no. No fear, fetching those children up? Actually we used to have, when I was here, we used to have two men living in and two girls. Yes. Two maids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 She didn't have any part time jobs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. Nothing whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How many rooms were there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well, here, there's five bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 This is the one you were living in first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Bowerbank, yes. There's five - five bedrooms, of course there's a toilet 
and bath room and everything upstairs. It's a little - well, in those days a modern house. A fine big kitchen, a dairy, there was a - a nice pantry and a - a lounge or sitting room and - there was four cellars underneath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So it was quite a big place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh it was a big house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. Oh yes, the men. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 The men who worked for your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. See there was two men that - that was the fifth bedroom you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And these were employees on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They were employed with the dairy work. And the two girls - there was two maids living in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Any relatives or lodgers at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, only come to stay that was all - holiday - oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Your mother did pay people to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, she had maids - two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How many servants were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Two - girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And they slept in one of the five bedrooms together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And you said that you all ate together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 In the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. We had one big kitchen - all the - one table only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And they would sit with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your mother supervise all the housework personally, she was always there working with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Yes, yes. She used to do all her own baking. There was no such a thing as - buying bread or - bread and everything twice a week. Oh yes. Tuesdays and Fridays. Used to be in a huge bowl on front - in front of the big old fire you know. Raisin
g - oh yes, lifting, yes. I think it - if I remembered - it was twenty' three loaves each time I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What kind of oven would she have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh it was the - there was the big old type open oven you know the - all the - well, I should think you 
could have three shelves on it it was that big in those days. Oh it was a lovely old house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you feel at ease with these two maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And how did servants and members of the family address each other - the children were addressed by their Christian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. And the - they - they addressed my father as mother - as - Mr and Mrs Wilson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you feel that any of them were interested in you as a person? You say that they were there when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, yes. The
y were always interested in us - we've - we more or less lived together, it was not a case of we - you're a maid or anything of that. No, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your mother give any moral guidance to her servants - you felt she probably would have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 She would do but of course I was only small enough to - well I know she must have done because they always came to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were they allowed any time to do just what they liked - were they allowed to go out when they liked and did they have their afternoons off?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well they used to have the afternoon or evening out but - they'd only got to ask and if if was a - a legitimate thing they would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were they local girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Well - Wooton girls both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Both from Liverpool - so they would have had their own homes to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, they used to go to their own homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did she mind what they did when they went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I know they used to like - we used to like them in by a certain time at night but - in those day
s you made your own pleasure and there was no such as a thing as going drinking or anything of that. I mean, even in my young days I can remember that - quite well. Yes, they used to make their own pleasure and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You wouldn't know much about who did the housework and what they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
It was normal household, yes. 'Course mind you there was the - there was such a thing as helping to wash up the cans and - and the tanks and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They would do that in addition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, and th
ey used to do all their own washing at the - every Monday morning they used to get up about half past five and start washing - 'course it was all in the boiler you see in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So the washing was done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 All the washing was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Who made or mended the family's clothes? Would your mother have made any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I think mother would do most of that, yes. Oh yes. Well, I daresay the girls would help but I - that's something I couldn't tell you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Not her. Oh - except breakfast, I think most - I think sometimes one of them used to help her to do the breakfast and things of that yes, but - all mother, yes, she did all her own baking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 She'd be well equipped to do that wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh, not half, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house? Would your father have done much in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, well, whatever was done to the house there was always a - a tradesman came in and did it. Oh yes, I mean, they had no tim
e for such a thing as that, you must remember that we were milking cows three times a day and delivering milk - twice a day. In the district. It was a busy day. It was from half past five in the morning 'til seven o'clock at night. Seven days a week. Wint
er and summer, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you and your brothers and sisters have any tasks to carry out regularly to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, not - not fixed tasks - mind you I had no brothers then. My brother died when he was seventeen months old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 This was your twin brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
My twin brother. But the three - I had three sisters living. No, I can't re - they - as they got older of course they did but they were only young when they left here, see, that's at the first house. Oh no, they were just - just kiddies, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would either of these maids have been responsible for the children do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - one of them used to take us to the morning service at - we were Baptists, we used to go to Dovedale church and one of them used to take us - as a - to church on a Sunday morning. Of course there was no kiddies service in those days. No. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What other jobs would they have done in relation to to children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I daresay they'd bath - help to bath them or dress them or such as that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh I can remember them - getting bathed with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Playing games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would they have ever taken you out anywhere apart from church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - I don't think so, no. We - went away on our holidays and such as that you know, mother and father and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would they come too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 One - one generally come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Just to help out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, well with the kiddies, yes, we used to go to Spain actually. I was twelve months old when I first went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You wouldn't know it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. Oh I've passed through it. More than once, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It's very built up now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh it is, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. No. He had his work cut outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And he kept to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh well, I mean, we had land as well you see in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So he was a busy man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you ever remember your father bathing you or dressing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I couldn't - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I daresay he did but not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. No, I think we always went together - mother and father. Yes, all the time, yes, very, very happy family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Nice to look back on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It is - very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you remember ever being looked after by your father - when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. Occasionally mum - my eldest - my eldest sister Hilda, she had a very, very nice voi
ce, well, and Margaret, the next one, and they used to go to singing concerts at Dovedale church. And of course I wasn't - one for concerts. I was more for going in the shippen and looking after the cows and - they used to go of an evening and we used - f
a
ther used to look after me and of course we was always in bed by half past seven. Yes, well of course, father was - when I was a boy about seven I was up at seven. But - after that when we - when we went to the other dairy - I was never in bed after half 
past five. No. Well I could still get up at half past five.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You've got thoroughly used to it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh nearly - all - all my life I've done it you see. I've been delivering milk sixty-three years. Started with cans from this dairy }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5113291\charrsid5983795 with a little tiny - little tin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
y dandy with a tank in - on a hook you know, and used to go down here before I went to school. And my first school was Bridge Road where - church school it was then. Of course Dovedale wasn't built then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I did ask you whether you had any tasks to carry out regularly and you felt you were a bit young at this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - what - the only tasks I had was I used to take milk of a morning. Yes, that's all, but never anything to do in the housework. I used to help father a little bit; I could and make myself really - clean the horses and such as that - what I could do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult such as dressing or undressing or look after them in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well there was not a great deal between three of them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They were quite close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Quite close and - they - the girls - of course I - I couldn't tell you really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way - can you remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays - you've told me that already?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 That was half past seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh, seven to half past, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh I daresay one of the maids would take us sometimes. Oh - oh yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What age did you put yourself to bed - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - eight or nine I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When I was - when we wer
e younger my eldest sister and I slept together. But - as I got older of course, I had my own room. And - there was a big room which three girls slept in, one with two beds, a double bed and a single bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And you slept in a double bed with your sister when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What were the sleeping arrangements for the rest of the family at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well father and mother - and the maids had - a - they had - the two maids slept together and the two men slept together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So you'd have you and your sister when you were small in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, one room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And the third bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well there was - you see, the two little girls was in cot with - in the big room with me mother 'cos the big room there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What room did you bath in - you mentioned you had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 But there weren't many people then with bathrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, we had bathroom and - W.C. separate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 That was really advanced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It was every Friday night. Friday night, bath night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When did you have clean clothes to put on - did it follow on from the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Saturday morning - general, yes. Or if we dirtied them in the week. Quite - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You mentioned that you always had your meals in the big kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you ever have them in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. Not - not - down here, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What about the other house when you moved when you were twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, I don't think - we always h
ad them - in the - well, it was a different type of kitchen at the other house - more like a dining room you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Where did your mother cook - she had the big range you mentioned where she cooked the bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. In the back kitchen. We had 
a proper back kitchen and - no, the bread was in the kitchen and the - but all the other cooking was on a gas stove actually. Yes, in the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - ah - I should think it used to range from seven 'til nine
. Seven 'til - half eight. Well the men and then father and us - us kiddies you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You wouldn't all have it together you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no, 'cos the men, when we were younger, the men would have it before we got up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would the family have it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - no, father would have it with the men. And - and the maids you see, probably we'd have it on our own - as kiddies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 With your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well mother's - her's earlier, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - for one thing me mother being Scotch it was porridge. Oat - oatmeal porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. And - bacon and egg or - or saus - sausage or - we had a cooked breakfast always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Winter and summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Winter and summer, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you have anything different to eat for breakfast on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - we used to always have sausage. Yes. Always sausage on a Sunday. And we always had a - a cold lunch on a Sunday 'cos father said they - father woul
d never let them do more work than was needful. Save the preparation, yes. There was - the - the - well it used to be a hindquarter or lamb with all of them you see and that was cooked on the Saturday and we had Saturday dinner hot and cold on a Sunday. Y
es, yes. Well no work was done on the farm - and amongst the cattle or anything only that absolutely was necessary. Yes, the minimum, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 The cows still had to be milked and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh, all that - I mean, oh Lord we used to have to deliver milk twice a day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your mother make her own jam or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well she didn't bottle fruit but she made her own jam. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did she make pickles or wine or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. We were all teetotal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Yes - a lit - well, when I was a boy we used to have - a field - which would have potatoes in and such as that you see and of course we'd all - always our own hens and we used to grow greens, vegetables, but not a great lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not self supporting in that way you mean - you would have bought some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh we had buy some definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you remember your mother buying tinned or dried vegetables or fruit when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well yes, we'd have tinned fruit for - for tea and such as that, oh yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Livesktock, you kept hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Cows and horses. Oh well we could - we used to tie up about twenty-three cows at - at the first dairy. Yes. I used to go in the shi
ppen about half past seven of - with a little apron on when I was six years of age to milk a cow. Try to learn to milk. And one morning I went in and they'd taken the cow to the slaughter house. And I broke me heart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did they tell you what had happened to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
They just said that they'd taken it away. Well it of course nearly dry you see and we - in those days we used to carve a few of our own but we used to buy them ready calved you see 'cos we had to have the production of milk all the time. Yes
, we had to keep that steady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lord no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you ever remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5113291\charrsid5983795 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 eeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more - and did your father have more to eat than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. We had just exactly all what we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember your mother ever having less of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes - we weren't - we weren't strict - not to that wa
y strict but - we had to know our place. I mean, there was - lot's of thing that there isn't today. There's no - there's no respect for age - for elders or such as that, but we had to know our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And this was felt at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, we used to - we learnt to - our manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - you had a - your choice really but - mother always put a - it was plain good wholesome food. And all
 her own pastry was cooked as - made herself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So you were expected mostly to eat what was put down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, well it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It was - if you've had enough well you've had enough and that was it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, you could ask. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - the right way of course, yes. Oh yes, oh yes. Yes. Because I know, although I wasn't as far as me spoon was concerne
d because I'm left handed - but - the only thing that - I was made to do with my left hand was to write at school. And - I know I had an awful job. Oh well, that's the only think I do now is writing with my right hand - it's all left. The left foot - foot
ball. Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
I - I daresay the girls used to bring a dolly with them but I can't ever remember with toys. Quite honestly I don't think I was ever much interested in toys. It was most animals. Amongst the cattle all the time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 If you asked you could leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Before everybody else had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Oh yes - well - within reason, yes, within reason.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It wasn't a strict rule that nobody was allowed to leave until everybody had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no. Father wasn't - wasn't that type of a man. He was a - a man for peace. Definitely for peace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you give me some examples of your midday meal - the sort of thing you would have had midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well we'd have a vegetable and lamb or beef or - oh always potatoes and we'd always have a boiled rice or - milk - pudding or sometimes we'd have a - roly-poly if you remember what that is, yes. Yes, roly-poly such as that. We had variety
. But we'd always a - a hot meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh that was only tea. High tea. Well with - as a rule we used to have just bread and butter and jam and cakes and such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What about the two men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh they had the same as us. Yes. They got a darned good meal - a good breakfast and a good midday meal and they didn't want it actually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you always have the same place at table - did you all sit down together for a meal - at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - when we weren't at school. Yes, oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, we always more or less stuck to our own places, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And you more or less went to the same seat each time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How was the meal served and by whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I think mother would dish it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would it be put onto dishes and put on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh father - yes - father - it was brought onto the table and father did the carving. And mother would - do the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would the maids have helped her serve out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh the ma
ids'd - probably pass it round or carry the things in or such as that. There was no such a thing as - the maid got to do this - that's it, oh no. It was home for all. It is, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What order were you served in - was your father served first or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Oh no, father would do all the cutting up. And he would more or less get his last I think. I think we would be served first to satisfy us and then the men and the girls and father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Where did the younger sisters sit before they c
ould feed themselves - can you remember any of them being small enough not to be able to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well we used to have high chair. Yes. Oh sit up in the high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would they have their meal at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, in other - oh yes, at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not fed before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not to my knowledge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It's difficult to remember isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It is, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 The servants would have had exactly the same food as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, very. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, she was Scotch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And she was quite demonstrative towards you was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, she was always - it hurt her more to hit us than it did to hurt us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It upset her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 If you had any worried could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, you could do anything with mother or father. Yes, both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Was your father an easy person to talk to as well as your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh father was very easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did he show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And if you'd had any worries you could have shared them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh could do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - we always - we always looked 
up to our parents and we - we tried to be obedience - as kiddies will be and - they were - well, they were lenient with us but they were - strict, not too strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You weren't allowed to do exactly as you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - well, to be kind and - and all just a - a family. Just a family, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you - can you remember their attitude to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - if it was unlawfully - that they hurt me - hurt us without any reason I think my mother used to get a little wild but - if -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would she tell you to go and hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Serves you right - you must have been doing something sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You mean that was her attitude more than the belligerent one?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No - if - there must have been something with you - both ways so that's it you see. Had to stand up for yourself. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I know, my own opinion was to grow up like my father and my mother. Yes, I think we all did. We all grew up -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - your
 life in - in the church was one and to be honest. And - well - to love more - to love one another more than hatred. There was no such a thing as hatred in either of my mother or my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 They were gentle were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. Very gentle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. Never heard either of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 If grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Just occasionally - not often. No, no. No, you had to keep your place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well, we should get severely told off and it if was really bad of course we'd get the punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You'd get a physical walloping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 By either parent or just by one would you have been punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I think my mother was more than father. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, I do. I - actually one of my sisters, Margaret, the middle one, she ran in to tel
l my mother I'd been down in an orchard at the bottom of Rose Bray and it - I'd been eating some apples. And I know mother come out in a terrible rage because I'd gone into this orchard and gave me a jolly good hiding. I know I was violently sick and it w
orried her stiff - she gave mea penny after. I could always remember that. Yes, conscience - thought she'd hurt me you see, and she thought he'd hurt me, yes, oh dear. but not - it was - there was very rarely any - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh Lord no, nothing like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember how you felt about being punished - how did you feel in this particular instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I felt hurt at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your 
parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, they both played the same part. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - a little bit, it wasn't a great - in those days of course you had a birthday but - the only one that counted was your twenty-first.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You didn't have - guests in to tea and a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh not - not as a - I can't remember - more - probably would have had little ones in but not to mym - no I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you have received presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well, I daresay your father and mother gave you a present but - those things I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on a Christmas Day when you were a chil
d - what sort of day would Christmas Day have been - what would you have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - Christmas Day of course there was always the - we used to get our toys and that you know in the morning. But - actually Christmas wasn't kept up as much as - New Years day with us. Scotch. And they always had a - their friends on New Year's Eve.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You had a big party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you have ever gone out to visit relatives on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, no, 'course we couldn't you see, we were always the farm, the farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you have relatives to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well, there might have been perhaps somebody but my - it was always kept - there was always a - a party for the men, mother always used to give them an extra special tea and the girls. That was
 done during the Christmas but it was - as a rule after the New Year's Eve you see. That was mother's day - father's and mother's day for their party - all the - my - I had an uncle and an auntie used to come down from Scotland and that and - oh yes, we u
sed to have - always Scottish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Who would have played that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - I'm sorry to tell you we all tried but none of us really - but we had - a phonograph. Actually we had 
a phonograph and - my sister and I both made recores. Sang - yes. Yes, mine was I think Here Comes the Sandman if I remember and my sisters was By Ma Colour Erin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And of course you said your sisters sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh my sisters ; oh I had a nice voice. Oh yes, yes, had a good voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You obviously all liked singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
We all liked singing. That was a thing often we used to do when we got older, especially on a Sunday evening well - after - when the war started, the first world war my father's two 
- two of my father's men went - left us and we'd only one, a cowman which lived out and - but used to come on a Sunday night that - my eldest sister next to me and myself and father would be milking the cattle in the evening - when we're milking three tim
es a day and - that was father - come on, sing up some to the hymns. Yes. And 1 the old Hundred and Abide with Me and all those we used to sing - my sister was - I had a tenor voice as a boy and my sister was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2110939\charrsid5983795 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2110939\charrsid5983795  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
fine soprano and father was - a bass. And we used to sing while we were milking the cattle. Yes, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Dominoes and rings. Do you remember rings? You - you'll know that rings are. You know there used to be a board on the wall with number
s. Yes, throw them, yes, yes. No, well I haven't. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What about books in the house, were there many books in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - I was never interested in books and - the sisters I think did a little but of course in the early days they w
ere too small. But of course I was more or less - in all animals - all my life. It's been all animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did your parents read many books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Father used to get a series of - these - what would they call them - sacred - magazines. There was the one c
alled the little gleaner. And the saw and there were - Christian books and he used to get them sent him each week. Yes. That was - and of course we got the Echo, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Any other magazines apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember your mother or father reading out loud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Oh I - father would sometimes when he had these Little Gleaner and things like that if we were all sitting he'd say, well here's a nice piece and he'd read this out to us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would your mother have read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, mother didn't read out to us much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 She didn't read much at all really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh she'd - just - just - now what was the one she had? She used to get it every week - it was from Mossley Hill 
church, it's something to do with the mothers union. Yes. Pamphlet thin-, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were small? Your own twin died but you wouldn't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh I don't remember any of those, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Anyone else in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
No, not as a boy I don't. No. No. I remember - well - well I don't - I wasn't there. My grandfather died - he was at Southport - he retired at - and went to Southport to live and we used to go there - we used to go there - my uncle an
d his family went one month and we went the other month and - I can remember that death but - of course I was - I wasn't at the funeral or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You can't remember any activity at home on the day of the funeral or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You didn't have the people coming back to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, not from Southport. No, no. No, it was done - he was buried in Southport.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When you were young were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well 
we went to relations but - were - never out in the evenings. And - we used to was a picnic to go to - this probably you won't know - there used to be a - a theatre out at - out Stoneycroft way - I can't think of the name of it now - which used to have the
 - a circus at Christmas and that was our treat. Yes, yes. Olympia. It was the Olympia - we used to go there and it - only - you could only get on the bus to Edghill church and you used to have to walk through. Yes. Well it was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You can't remember being taken out to see friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Just to the grandfather - no, no, not - oh no, not in the evenings. No. Well, they were never out much - my father or mother, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, he used to go to auctions and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 He took you along with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you remember any outings at all with your parents. There were no - Bank Holiday for you?
