\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, the only - the o
nly - sing - singing - singling out was - when there was a scholarship class. Anybody was - for to go through for scholarships. I was never one of the bright ones from that point of view. But mind you when I was thirteen and a half - well I was nearly fou
rteen - I only went to school in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You mentioned this didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You used to go and deliver the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. I got - used to deliver milk from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You did that since you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Thi
s was well, you see, that was starting on the first world war. We were at Hillside dairy then and father - both of father's men went and I had to take a - an active part, see, we'd cows - we'd twenty-seven cows there and we'd ninety acres of land which we
 
worked - that was Calderstones and Hartlill Estate and the - there was a field in Ollerton Road - believe it or not - full length to the - Gaumont is. That was all fields. And we used to graze our cows there. Used to milk three times a day - matter of fac
t
 my young - the sister next to me used to help us to milk. Yes. Yes, that was in - not in the morning. I used to have to milk six or seven cows in the morning and deliver milk then go to school and come home, have me lunch and - did - milk the dinner time
 and then take a horse and float from our area as far as the Cathedral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 This would take you all afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. From about half past one - two o'clock to about five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You started doing that when you were about thirteen and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 About thirteen and a half to fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you leave school at fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Were there any gangs or groups in this school - Dovedale Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, I wouldn't - there was no - there was no such a thing as gangs in - I can ever remember. There's - there was not an act to ga}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868538\charrsid5983795 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
ging up against anybody else sort of thing. There was certain - those who were keen on football and cricket, well of course the masters and that played with us as you know and that was the only if you call - that'
s not ganging. No, there was no such a thing as ganging or spiting or anything of that. There was no such a thing as spite. It is - well of course, there was discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Can you remember any children who were left out of things at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You were fourteen when you left school - would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity to do so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No - I wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you attend any part time education afterwards - any evening school or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - sometimes yes and sometimes no. I mean - you do - I think everybody has some regrets and - nothing that I would be really - worried about. I had quite - very happy - young life. Very happy young life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When you sometimes regret your schooling what occasions would you regret it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well - probably I should have learnt more and that. As I told you before my best subject was arithmetic and the others weren't too good. I suppose s
tandard but - there's many a thing - many a time now I wish I had have gone in further for maths, yes. Yes, 'course you can't do everything when you were working and during the war. War coming strike out on top of you you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Circumstances play such a part in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 It did - those circumstances did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And people who were young in the last war were affected like this too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Quite - yes, yes, they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12868538\charrsid5983795 Oh definitely benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 ed, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
While you were at school - this part time job which you had - of course you - apart from when you stopped going to school in the afternoon at thirteen and a half you had been a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, working at home with father and mother. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you earn any money from this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I think I used to get about a shilling a week. Yes. Pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How did you feel about the work - you obviously enjoyed working with animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Definitely. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You enjoyed the work side of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I've never - I wouldn't mind being amongst animals now. Not at my age - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did working alter you attitude to school whilst you were doing this part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not as I know of, no. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 When you were fourteen did you stay with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 All the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
All the time. Yes. We started - a seven day a week - we started about - quarter past five in the morning and we finished at seven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You wouldn't get anyone to do that now would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What exactly did you do when you started working full time with your father - did you do anything extra that you hadn't done before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - oh yes, we - you see, I used to - order me milk of the m
orning and then deliver milk. But when I left school of course the cows were to be fed and - cleaned and - all the hay an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10911137\charrsid5983795 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
 stuff and in summer there was the - the hay got and cut and grass to be carted and all kinds of things like that. According to the stock. General farm work - yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you have any holidays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you still go away with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes - no, I didn't go with my parents then. I went with an auntie and uncle. With my auntie and my cousin. That was the 
one that was left here when I was born and they - see - we used to have to divide it up 'cos when I was - got turned fourteen I used to - if they wanted to go away I used to come and help them to deliver milk down here - used to divide it between the two 
places. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 What did your father pay you when you first started - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I think it was about ten shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - yes, 'course I got everything. I mean, clothes and everything and fed. That was pocket money, yes. Yes, spend as I want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You didn't have to give any of that to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would your father have taken on any more employees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. Oh there was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Very well. We had a - we had a cowman and a man that used to help on the land. After the - there was two men there first and then they - and then the - this cowman he was with us all during the war. Oh yes, 'til over - well - he must have 
been with us 'til I was about twenty-seven - twenty-eight. Oh I got on very well with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did working full time alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well I - quite honestly I think I was glad it was over. I was quite happy - no, no, quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You were with your father up 'til the time he died or did you marry before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh I was - no, I was with me father 'til they took me to the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How old were you when you went into the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I was - I had to go and enlist when I was ei
ghteen. 1918. Yes. Well then - my father got a twelve month's exemption for me because I was in agriculture although I was passed category A.I. Well I was twenty - I was nineteen on the twenty-first of may and I was called up on the twenty-third. And they
 
- they shipped me off to Ireland. I was at Victoria Barracks, Cork. I was there eleven months. But during that time - I was very fortunate to be quite honest because - we - did our sixteen weeks training ready for France and we had to go to a place called
 
Yule, I daresay you know of it - in South - below - it's thirty miles South of Cork and we'd to fire our course there and it was a lovely little seaside place and this was all strictly private and there was a lovely beech. We used to fire onto this beach 
i
nto the sea. And after - in the summer it was, it was in the June - June or July - July I think it was, anyway - and - after the - you'd fired so many rounds if it was a very nice day they'd let you go and have a swim. Well of course, bathing costumes or 
n
ot it wouldn't mattered then because you were all boys and - that's it. And I - we were playing in the water and that and a fellow picked me up by the feet and threw - put me in head first and I spit - four false teeth I had here out in me - in the sea an
d
 I lost them. Well when I went back - when I went back to the barracks they - told me I had to go on dental treatment and that saved me from going to France. Yes. I was doing - being a fully qualified trained soldier then but I was doing fatigues - lookin
g
 after - I think it was - about eighteen - twenty-one men I think it was in - in the room - keeping the room and - and getting their meals and all that. And - doing escort duties. I came to Mole for a deserter. And I was detailed - this was in - the end o
f
 August, I was detailed to come to - Dell Street with a sergeant for a deserter in Dale Street. Anyway this - there was an agricultural order came out that all agriculturalists had to be remain in barracks to go and help for the harvesting you see. And I 
w
as taken off this and so was the sergeant. He was put in charge of getting us all together and - the poor chappies that went was - blown up on the Linster. Torpedoes. Never heard of - either of them. So there you are. Circumstances again, yes. I got home 
t
hen - got home on - on - agricultural leave. Well I got - between my - our place and the farm out at - Greenhill Road. The big farm that used to be on the end of Greenhill Road. Used to have to go - do our place in the morning with my father in the mornin
g
 and over there in the afternoon. And that's - well, I was - I was attached to the Army 'til - 'til the following April. 1920. And I was out on the - I got out in the May. Being the - I think the - classified me as pivot - pivotal man - a pivotal man or s
omething they call them and I got out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 And from then you worked again with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh right back with me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 How long would you work for him for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh - always. Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So you really haven't done anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, nothing in me life. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 But you're retired now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Retired now, yes. But that was up to - 1918 - that's what you wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 But we want your jobs up to the present day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes, yes, oh well I was still in the same trade - job. I've been in this job - I've done - delivered milk for sixty-three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Which is a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well it is to be going on with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Have you done anything else at all ever - any part time jobs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 NO. NO.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
No. No. The only - the only occupation I would have like to have been actually on a farm. To have my own proper farm and not deliver milk. You know. The whole day up to animals, yes. Yes, calving cattle and breeding and such as 
that. I did breed two ponies - two horses, you know. I had a mare with two foals, yes. Peggy. Do you remember First Peggy. Well she had two foals. Yes. That's the one there. I had some photographs of the foals somewhere. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5449934\charrsid5983795 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 ation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. The only - the only - the organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5449934\charrsid5983795 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 ation was the Cow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5449934\charrsid5983795 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
keepers Association, but that was nothing to do with unions or anything of that. It was just a - our own trade. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you feel that - there were divisions of interest among workers in those early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Well quite honestly they seemed to be very happy. They're much happier than they are today - they - they got on with the work and enjoyed it. I - can't ever remember much grumbling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Some people say that there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - a - a craftsman was a craftsman and a labourer was a labourer but I don't think they were treated in the same way as they are today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 There wasn't a great division between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
No, I don't think there was a great division - the one helped the other. A craftsman knew if he had has mate as they call them - well, they worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. I don't think so. NO, I was very happy and I was happy as a child. I was quite happy at me work - very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You did continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Or with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. We were always very happy - really happy family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you spend your Sunday any differently when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No - we - of course we didn't have to do quite as much work and we went to church with the family - just the same. Same sort of pattern.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you stop going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well of course I was working in afternoon then you see, y
es. Actually I was delivering milk in Mavill Road - you know where Mavill is don't you? You know Queens Drive - Mavill is the next one - up on the far side of Ollerton Road. Well I was delivering milk there when - when the papers came round with the war d
eclared - Sunday afternoon three o'clock, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you take an interest in politics at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You were too young to vote weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you vote at all before 1919?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, no. We couldn't 'til we was twenty-one you know. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You weren't a member of a political party were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No. No. No. I've never been a member of any party except I vote - my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You told me earlier of something of how you spent your spare time - bicycling and playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things now you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - probably - we used to - perhaps go to the pictures once a week or something like that and - in summer - if we 
had any time we used to play cricket. And I was very keen on tennis - very keen. Sports - all sports - sports played a great part in my life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Apart from the pictures did you go out in the evening anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 No, I don't think - well only in summer. Winter we didn't much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Who would you have gone to the pictures with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 I suppose - friends - lads and probably one or two girls and such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you make any new friends at this time in your life - boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Not - no, I think it was more or less as we'd - from the late schooling to - kept within the same crowd, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You were encouraged to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes, we were encouraged to bring our friends home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did you have any really special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well there was - I had two boy friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 These were friends at school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Yes. Yes, and that and then of course one of them left Mossley Hill and - 'course - then 1914 to '18 it 
was more or less the war and - it was a case of work. Work and sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Your parents did expect to meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Oh yes. Yes, there was - yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Did they expect to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - no, I don'
t think - they didn't want you out at all hours of night if want to your bed because then you had to bet up in the morning. If we went to the pictures perhaps we'd be - in before half past nine - ten o'clock at night. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 You wouldn't be out later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 
Oh no. Unless it was a dance and - 'course that came later on in life - about twenty-two or twenty-three and playing football with a club then, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1382998 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 So you'd have a dance afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid418543 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14944617\charrsid5983795 Well - on a Saturday night - I belonged t
o three - two or three clubs then. Two clubs - St Barnabas was one and - the Dovedale Brotherhood was the other.
